meanings.definition: To run faster than someone or something.
meanings.sent1: She outrung her friend in the race.
meanings.sent2: The cheetah outrung the gazelle in the chase.
meanings.sent3: The tortoise outrung the hare in the unexpected race.
meanings.sent4: His determination outrung all obstacles in his path.
meanings.sent5: The wind outrung the storm, swiftly moving ahead.

meanings.sent1: He outrung his previous record in the marathon.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outrung his competitors in the last race.
meanings.sent3: The snail outrung all expectations and won the race.
meanings.sent4: Her memory of the event outrung any doubts in her mind.
meanings.sent5: The river outrung its banks after heavy rainfall.
